Dear Senator Bond: 

I am aware that a hearing has been scheduled on November 10 before the Senate 
Commerce, Science, and Transportation Subcommittee on Aviation pertaining to the 
Wright  Amendment  and  certain  restrictions  on  commercial  airline  flights  operating 
out  of  Love  Field  in  Dallas.  The  purpose  of  this  letter  is  to  support  the  creation  of 
an  additional  exception  to  the  Amendment  that  would  allow  direct  flights  between 
Missouri and Love Field. 

